OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1782152300
OL,3,CWhat happens now Keir Starmer has
OL,4,Cresigned?
OL,6,FThen, they need to receive nominations
OL,7,Ffrom either 5% of constituency Labour
OL,8,Fparties, or three affiliated
OL,9,Forganisations (which must include two
OL,10,Ftrade unions), which represent 5% of
OL,11,Faffiliated membership.
OL,13,FOnly after passing those two stages
OL,14,Fwill candidates go before the party
OL,15,Fmembership.
OL,17,FIn Labour's 126-year history, there
OL,18,Fhas never been an official leadership
OL,19,Fchallenge mounted against a sitting
OL,20,Fprime minister.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
