PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1782152300
OL,3,CWhat happens now Keir Starmer has
OL,4,Cresigned?
OL,6,FA contender is declared the winner if
OL,7,Fthey get more than 50% of first
OL,8,Fpreferences, and this usually happens
OL,9,Fthrough a process of elimination
OL,10,Fduring rounds of voting, the timetable
OL,11,Ffor which is set by Labour's ruling
OL,12,FNational Executive Committee (NEC).
OL,14,FHow long will this take?
OL,16,FIn his resignation speech, Starmer
OL,17,Fsaid that nominations will open on
OL,18,FJuly 9 and close before summer recess
OL,19,Fon July 16.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
